OL,7,FThe court was also told that Mr Dymond
OL,8,Fsaw a nurse practitioner on April 10,
OL,9,Fwhen he asked for a letter to say he
OL,10,Fwas not depressed or taking anti-
OL,11,Fdepressants so that he could go on a
OL,12,Ftelevision show to take a lie detector
OL,13,Ftest.
OL,15,FHe had handed back the anti-
OL,16,Fdepressants unused, but the nurse
OL,17,Frefused to write the letter.
